Notebook[{
Cell["SyntheticInfrageometry", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"bb28de64-b107-4dd9-8f53-47d8901c080d"],

Cell["\<\
SyntheticInfrageometry organizes Euclidean (metric), path-space (selectors), \
coordinatization, Tarski (betweenness + equidistance), projective \
(incidence), tropical convexity (graph-only), Alexandrov / \
comparison-triangle, metric algebra, and visualization layers around \
multivalued constructions on graphs and hypergraphs. Every direction has a \
Guide (categorical overview) and a Tutorial (worked walkthrough). This master \
guide is the entry point.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"86dbd888-1109-45d1-a2e5-14136a6061f0"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"76685b1e-447e-46af-a945-a3f914fc857d"],

